text: Dominik Crête (born July 7, 1991) is a Canadian kayaker who competes primarily in the sprint distances. Crête is the reigning Pan American Games champion in the K-1 200 m distance. He started kayaking at the age of 11 but quit to focus on football. A meeting with Olympian Richard Dober Jr. in 2015 convinced him to return to the sport of kayaking. Crête studied police techniques at CEGEP de Trois-Rivières and currently works as a special constable for Hydro-Quebec. ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Canadian male canoeists Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Trois-Rivières Category:Canoeists at the 2019 Pan American Games Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for Canada Category:Pan American Games medalists in canoeing
